# QMK Git submodules

Libraries under `lib/` (e.g. `lib/chibios-contrib`) are **submodules**. The parent repo stores one **commit SHA** per submodule, not the library’s files as normal paths.

## What `modified: lib/… (new commits)` means

The submodule directory is checked out at a **different commit** than the one your current QMK revision records—often after `git pull` inside the submodule, a branch switch there, or an incomplete submodule update.

`git submodule status` shows **`+`** in the first column when the checked-out commit does not match the parent’s recorded SHA.

## Default fix (match upstream QMK)

Reset the named submodule to the pin:

```bash
git submodule update lib/chibios-contrib
```

After `git pull` in **qmk_firmware**, keep everything aligned:

```bash
git submodule sync --recursive
git submodule update --init --recursive
```

## When you intentionally want a newer submodule

Only if you are forking/customizing QMK: keep the newer checkout, then from the repo root `git add lib/<name>` and commit so the parent records the new SHA.

## Inspect drift

```bash
git ls-tree HEAD lib/chibios-contrib   # commit parent expects
cd lib/chibios-contrib && git rev-parse HEAD   # commit checked out
```
